		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=61546"><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>1254 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.70]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Bard mezz spells, like Pixie Strike and Sinioche's Dream have a knockback component and not a stun component - so they work on 55+ mobs that are immune to stun.&nbsp;&nbsp;Its the knockback that interrupts spell casting.<br><br>True, you cannot charm a PC in PVP but you can charm other mobs and send them after the PC or his/her pet.  I haven't tried it but I think you can charm the pet.<br><br>At the highest levels of the game a well played bard cannot lose a PvP fight - only draw.  Winning is another issue.  Again, a draw is more likely.  In the lower levels of the game straight melees vs a bard will usually lose since the bard has range spell attacks that can be cast on the move.  Many bard songs have a range that is better than an un-focused spell caster (but a extended range focus item can make up for this).  Bard snare songs, mezz songs, etc will allow a bard who is losing to escape before being killed. Even a rooted bard is not completely immobile due to Melonies Malifluos Motion.  <br><br>But most bards are not PvP.  EQ was mainly designed as a PvE game.  So worry more about PvE strategies when rating how good a class is to play.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=4><img src=/shared/root_thread_ic